sec.p:
Four widely-used yeast microarray datasets were first examined:
Spellman-alpha, the alpha-factor arrested cell cycle dataset from Spellman et al. (12);
Spellman-cdc15, the cdc15 arrested cell cycle dataset from Spellman et al. (12);
Zhu-alpha, the alpha-factor blocked cell cycle dataset from Zhu et al. (13);
Diauxic-shift, the diauxic shift dataset from DeRisi et al. (14);

Since all four experiments analyzed so far were published at least five years ago, it is interesting to see whether the chip artifact has diminished with the advance of microarray technology. Therefore, we analyzed three newly-published microarray experiments in three different organisms performed by three independent labs:
Yeast, the microarray karyotyping dataset from Dunn et al. (20);
Worm, the ER stress response dataset from Viswanathan et al. (21);
Human, the colon cancer dataset from Giacomini et al. (22);
